tests/svelte-5-derived-by.test.js import { render, fireEvent, screen } from '@testing-library/svelte'; import DerivedByComponent from '../src/components/DerivedByComponent.svelte'; import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'; describe('DerivedByComponent', () => { it('renders with initial values', () => { render(DerivedByComponent); const input = screen.getByTestId('text-input'); const wordCount = screen.getByTestId('word-count'); const charCount = screen.getByTestId('char-count'); const lengthIndicator = screen.getByTestId('length-indicator'); const clearButton = screen.getByTestId('clear-button'); expect(input).toBeInTheDocument(); expect(input).toHaveValue(''); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 0'); expect(charCount).toHaveTextContent('Characters: 0'); expect(lengthIndicator).toHaveTextContent('Status: Short text'); expect(clearButton).toBeInTheDocument(); }); it('updates derived values when text changes', async () => { render(DerivedByComponent); const input = screen.getByTestId('text-input'); const wordCount = screen.getByTestId('word-count'); const charCount = screen.getByTestId('char-count'); const lengthIndicator = screen.getByTestId('length-indicator'); await fireEvent.input(input, { target: { value: 'Hello Svelte 5 runes!' } }); expect(input).toHaveValue('Hello Svelte 5 runes!'); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 4'); expect(charCount).toHaveTextContent('Characters: 21'); expect(lengthIndicator).toHaveTextContent('Status: Short text'); await fireEvent.input(input, { target: { value: 'This is a much longer sentence to test the word count derivation.' } }); expect(input).toHaveValue('This is a much longer sentence to test the word count derivation.'); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 13'); expect(charCount).toHaveTextContent('Characters: 65'); expect(lengthIndicator).toHaveTextContent('Status: Short text'); // Input enough words to trigger the "Long text" status await fireEvent.input(input, { target: { value: 'Word one two three four five six seven eight nine ten eleven twelve thirteen fourteen fifteen sixteen seventeen.' } }); expect(input).toHaveValue('Word one two three four five six seven eight nine ten eleven twelve thirteen fourteen fifteen sixteen seventeen.'); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 17'); expect(charCount).toHaveTextContent('Characters: 118'); expect(lengthIndicator).toHaveTextContent('Status: Long text'); }); it('clears the text and resets derived values when clear button is clicked', async () => { render(DerivedByComponent); const input = screen.getByTestId('text-input'); const clearButton = screen.getByTestId('clear-button'); const wordCount = screen.getByTestId('word-count'); const charCount = screen.getByTestId('char-count'); const lengthIndicator = screen.getByTestId('length-indicator'); await fireEvent.input(input, { target: { value: 'Some text to clear' } }); expect(input).toHaveValue('Some text to clear'); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 4'); expect(charCount).toHaveTextContent('Characters: 18'); await fireEvent.click(clearButton); expect(input).toHaveValue(''); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 0'); expect(charCount).toHaveTextContent('Characters: 0'); expect(lengthIndicator).toHaveTextContent('Status: Short text'); }); it('handles whitespace correctly for word count', async () => { render(DerivedByComponent); const input = screen.getByTestId('text-input'); const wordCount = screen.getByTestId('word-count'); await fireEvent.input(input, { target: { value: ' leading and trailing spaces ' } }); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 5'); await fireEvent.input(input, { target: { value: 'multiple spaces between words' } }); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 4'); await fireEvent.input(input, { target: { value: ' singleword ' } }); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 1'); await fireEvent.input(input, { target: { value: ' ' } }); expect(wordCount).toHaveTextContent('Words: 0'); }); });
